org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy

Class SeRequestSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.SeRequestSet

  • public final class SeRequestSet
extends java.lang.Object
    Aggregates one or more SeRequests to a local or remote SE Reader, sent through a ProxyReader, in order to open a logical channel with a SE application to select, and to transfer a group of APDU commands to run.
    See Also:
    SeResponseSet

      • SeRequestSet

        public SeRequestSet(java.util.Set<SeRequest> seRequests)
        Create an SeRequestSet from a list of SeRequests.
        • A SeRequestSet could contain several SeRequest to manage the selection of different types of PO application.
        • To exchange APDU commands with a soecific selected PO application a single SeRequest is necessary.
        Parameters:
        seRequests - List of SeRequests
